    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-06-18T10:45:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-06-18T10:45:00-05:00" n="675"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d675">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.20 Defense(M)/13533: Airgram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Venezuela</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Corrigan</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Caracas</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-06-18T11:15:00-04:30"
                            >June 18, 1943—11:15 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 21—3 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>A–333. For Rosenthal, BEW,<note n="38" xml:id="d675fn38">Morris Rosenthal,
                        Assistant Director, Board of Economic Warfare.</note> from Eisenhardt.<note
                        n="39" xml:id="d675fn39">Karl J. Eisenhardt, Field Representative of Board
                        of Economic Warfare.</note> Department’s A–645 of June 10<note n="40"
                        xml:id="d675fn40">Not printed.</note> advising delay of cinchona survey
                    until conclusion <pb facs="0819" n="805" xml:id="pg_805"/> of rainy season, we
                    strongly recommend that you reconsider your decision and make arrangements for
                    promptest possible start.</p>
                <p>We have thoroughly checked reliable sources information regarding transportation
                    in prospective cinchona areas and have ascertained that no important delays will
                    be encountered even during heaviest rainy season. Furthermore, we consider that
                    further delays will have detrimental effect on interest already aroused locally
                    for collaboration with our program.</p>
                <p>We anxiously await your further advices on this matter. [Eisenhardt.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Corrigan</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
